record.text: For example, I have observed several attempts to create informal record fields and create new features based on this common promise among third parties. So, they should be made easily extensible so that developers can easily test their pilot studies.

The difficulty with the AT Protocol and Bluesky API wrappers is that due to the flexibility of the Record, it's not possible to meet the needs of developers by creating only entity objects that wrap only the fields provided by the official Lexicon.
